J. Crew is a clothing retailer that operates 296 stores. The company operates as a multichannel specialty retailer of women’s, men’s, and children’s apparel, shoes, and accessories primarily in the United States and Canada. It offers an assortment of women’s… MoreJ. Crew is a clothing retailer that operates 296 stores. The company operates as a multichannel specialty retailer of women’s, men’s, and children’s apparel, shoes, and accessories primarily in the United States and Canada. It offers an assortment of women’s and men’s apparel and accessories, including outerwear, loungewear, wedding attire, swimwear, shoes, bags, belts, hair accessories, and jewelry under the J.Crew brand. The company also provides casual T-shirts and broken-in chinos; Italian cashmere and leather items; and hand-beaded skirts and double-faced cashmere jackets under the J.Crew brand.

J Crew was acquired by TPG Capital and Leonard Green & Partners and merged with the subsidiary Chinos Holdings in 2011.
