2013 and Earlier:
IT Priorities:
•J. Crew is in the midst of upgrade products for many of its SAP modules, including the supply chain (SCM), business intelligence (BW/BI), and Retail solutions.
•The company has made the development and support of its web and mobile eCommerce systems a continual priority.
•The company is currently preparing for upgrades to its network and data center operations.
•The company is looking into a BYOD implementation, with security as its main concern.
•Upcoming storage projects include automating backups cleaner, converting backups off tape to disk, and increasing storage capacity to keep up with storage demand.
•J. Crew maintains an ongoing server virtualization effort.

IT Structure:
•While the bulk of IT staff are located at the company's New York headquarters, a small IT team operates out of the company's distribution and call center location in Lynchburg, VA.
•J. Crew manages both its retail and eCommerce operations through the IT department.

IT Intelligence Snippets:
2013:
•The organization currently stores data volumes in the 100 tb – 1 pb range, and expects unstructured storage to grow more than 20% over the next 12 months.
•J. Crew primarily manages its operations using SAP systems, including supply chain, ERP, and human resources solutions focused on retail operations.
•J. Crew's mobile device management system supports BlackBerry, Android, and Apple mobile systems.
•The company has an agreement with Electronic Data Systems to provide enterprise infrastructure services. This includes hosting services and support for the infrastructure of enterprise merchandising and financial systems as well as distribution and call center infrastructure.
•The company maintains an outsourcing contract to manage its retail help desk operations.
•The company hosts its distribution and call center primarily in Lynchburg, VA. Mainframe computers host current inventory and order information for customer service associates assisting shoppers.





